3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the computational complexity of the proposed attack procedures. 
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the potential impact of the proposed cryptosystem on society, as it could lead to more secure and efficient communication. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper may be of interest to software engineers who are involved in implementing cryptographic algorithms.
